    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI have set laststatus to 0, because i only want to have stuff in a winbar. This works fine, as long as i split vertically, as soon as i have a window split horizontally the statusline shows up on the \"top\" window (screenshot added).\r\nTo me the section in the docs on laststatus indicates, that this is not intended behaviour, which is why i am filing a bug report. I have not found similar issues in the currently open ones.\r\n\r\nno horizontal split (all good):\r\n![nohorizontalsplit](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/74120050/4680a3df-32dc-4712-9649-b2092bfe1a4b)\r\n\r\nwith horizontal split (statusline visible on the right side):\r\n![withhorizontalsplit](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/74120050/f93c7e92-8c9e-42de-bd2b-3550c758e637)\r\n\r\n(also another thing that kind of threw me off, was that one had to use vim.g.statusline_winid in the function for drawing the winbar, but thats alright to me, maybe add docs for that somewhere down the road to eliminate confusion?)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. put stuff in your winbar globally (like \"%t\")\r\n2. set laststatus to 0 globally\r\n\r\nsnippet i used for winbar:\r\n```lua\r\n    _G.winbar = M.winbar\r\n    vim.opt.laststatus = 0\r\n    o.winbar = \"%!v:lua.winbar()\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI would expect the statusline to never show up when laststatus is set to 0\r\n\r\ndocs (options.txt):\r\n```\r\n\tThe value of this option influences when the last window will have a\r\n\tstatus line:\r\n\t\t0: never\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-35e3883 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1693350652\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno idea\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nNixOS\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nfoot 1.16.2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nnix neovim nightly overlay: https://github.com/nix-community/neovim-nightly-overlay",
